:Entry:  cv_float_check_: 02/01/83  cv_float_check_


Function: takes an ASCII representation of a floating point number and
returns a code indicating the possibility of a conversion error.  (See
also cv_float_ and cv_float_double_.)


Usage (with double precision):
declare cv_float_check_ entry (char(*) fixed bin(35)) returns
     (float bin);
a = cv_float_check_ (string);

Usage (with single precision):
declare cv_float_check_ entry (char(*) fixed bin(35)) returns
     (float bin);
a = cv_float_check_ (string);


Arguments:
string
   is the string to be converted.  (Input)
code
   is a code that equals 0 if no error has occurred; otherwise, it is
   the index of the character of the input string that terminated the
   conversion.  See "Note" below.
a
   is the result of the conversion.  (Output)

Notes:
Code is not a standard status code.  Therefore, it can not be passed to
com_err_ and other subroutines that accept only standard status codes.
